22,http://www.armslist.com/posts/2939022,For Sale:  Ruger MKII MK10 22lr Target Bull Barrel MK II MK 10,"Garland, Dallas, Texas",FREE,"Listed On: Monday, October 27, 2014",Handguns,Ruger                                                                                ,22 Long Rifle                                                                                ,Single Action                                                                                ,Pistol,"For sale or trade is a Ruger MKII Model MK10 .22lr semi-auto pistol, these are much harder to find than other models. This model has the 10” bull barrel and target sights, it is in very nice condition and bluing looks great, the only marks are a couple right around the chamber, but nothing serious, just want to be as accurate as I can. Not in a hurry to get rid of this one as it will only go up in value, but I have a few other .22lr pistols and rifles, so putting this up to see what is out there.  Who needs a .22lr rifle when you have this beauty, if you look at 22lr ballistics, the 10"" barrel gives you close to the same velocity as the 16""-19"" rifle length barrels.  This will allow you to get rifle like performance from a pistol.  You can also have it tapped for a scope for longer target shooting or varmint hunting.
$600 cash or might consider good trades.

If wanting to trade, please state what you have and exactly what you want to do, straight trade, trade +/- cash, other firearms, ammo, optics, etc. either way, so I know the deal.  I have other items listed as well.
Trades:
FN SCAR 16 and 17 or AR uppers in .450 Bushmaster, maybe .50 Beowulf
H&K USP or prefer larger frames like the Tactical or Expert models.
Saiga rifles in all calibers will be considered, converted or not.
Quality AR-15 or AR-10 rifles.
Maybe a 10mm, 1911 style??  Also, Glock 20 Gen 4 or SF, G23 and G32.
All makes & models of semi-auto rifles, AK-47, AK-74, SKS(Norinco & Russian) Saiga rifles and shotguns, PSL, FAL, AR-10, AR-15 and variants like Sig 556 etc. Maybe an M92 with arm brace just because.
All makes & models of semi-auto pistols or revolvers in .357 mag & .44 mag.
Another Mossberg 590A1 or 930 SPX.
Maybe bolt-guns in the common calibers, or quality low to higher power range scopes, quality red dots and magnifiers.

Maybe ammo in the popular calibers to help make a deal happen, but not going to give full retail value on ammo as I have plenty already.  Will consider .308/7.62x51, 7.62x39, 7.62x54, 5.45x39(7n6), .223/5.56, 9mm, .45ACP, .357 Sig, .357 Mag, .44 Mag and .22lr.
Ftf in or around Garland area, but I do make trips to Arlington and Lewisville area on occasion.  Must be legal to own a firearm in TX.  Will ship if needed."

38,http://www.armslist.com/posts/2939038,For Sale/Trade:  COLT LE6920 M4 with LOTS of extras,"NE Wichita, Wichita, Kansas","$ 2,500","Listed On: Sunday, April 13, 2014",Rifles,Colt                                                                                ,223/5.56 NATO                                                                                ,Semi-automatic                                                                                ,Rifle,"I have a fully decked-out Milspec Colt M4 for sale with about 50 perfect rounds through it - not a single malfunction of any kind, like you would expect from a Colt. I purchased this rifle brand new last September and have just not used it much. I spent several months getting all of the extras for it, but now I don't really have much use for it. This is a brand new condition, quality, top-of-the-line rifle with all top quality parts and extras. I have included a detailed list below of everything that comes with the rifle.

column2: Milspec Colt M4 rifle with milspec marked parts and magpul FDE furniture
New EOTech 512 with box and batteries (perfect co-witness with iron sights)
Surefire 6P tactical flashlight with momentary on-off button or twist for permanent on (comes with 2 extra unused batteries
Angled aluminum mount for tactical light
Aluminum extended quad rail (extends beyond gas block to allow for placing accessories farther up along the barrel)
5 1/2 sets of Magpul rail covers (mix of FDE, OD Green, and Black - I have them currently aligned in a digi-camo pattern). I also have some rubber rail covers that come with the rifle.
4 windowed 30-round pmags (2 FDE, 2 black) – 3 with dust covers
Harris style bipod with extending legs w/twist-on leg lock
New heavy duty rifle case with extra padding, multiple pockets for accessories, and internal straps for securing the rifle
270 rounds of specialty ammo (130 rounds of brass hornady vmax, 22 rounds of tracers, 118 of brass armor piercing rounds); I also have several strip clips included
Fake silencer/mussel brake (very nice for adding stability; noticeable difference in barrel rise/recoil); I also have the stock flash suppressor included

Other miscellaneous accessories include: upgraded rubber stock pad, 45 degree angled picatinny rail mount, strap mount for picatinny rail, rifle cleaning kit (oils, brushes, cloths, etc), 2 snap caps, swivel bipod mount, lens cloth for EOTech

column1: I hesitate to let this go since it is THE rifle setup that I've wanted for a while, but like I said, I just found I don't have much use for it and would rather have the cash. I'm asking $2500 OBO for everything. If interested, shoot me an email or text at 316-seven34-1638."
